<p>A few very good tips - I generally prefer not to look at the light show - partivularly once you get to raiding levels, this can cause lag, and be hard to follow at times. I follow the casting bar, personally. As for hotkeys - I prefer to manually twist, due to missed notes, and the fact that I tend to adapt my twist based on what is going on - if I see that someone can't land a slow, I will start twisting Occlusion of Sound, and throw on a Requiem of Time, to tide the group over until a slow lands. Again - it's all preferance. Many bards prefer hotkeys, many prefer the flexibility of manual twisting. It's all in play styles.</p>
