<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />I did not see a description of this hotkey, but it would seem the least problematic:&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />Melody  <br /> <br />/melody #.#.#.#  <br /> <br /> <br />In place of the # of course is your song slot number.  If it misses a note just hit the hotkey again. Allows greater freedom to melee and with the new bandolier for weapons/instruments and a hotkey for them, makes for much smoother enjoyable playing :)<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />There is a major hole in that tactic though. We get a lot of missed notes (until you get the right AAs at least). If you just rehit that hotkey everytime you get a missed note, you're going to be stuck singing 2 or 3 songs most of the time, maybe getting lucky enough to get through an entire 4 song cycle on occasion.</p>
